properties.headline: Anzac Day Dawn Service & March - Sunday 25 April - SYDNEY CBD Martin Place, Elizabeth Street, Liverpool Street
properties.publicTransport: Additional early morning services will run. Travel on public transport is free for veterans and their families. Buses in the city will be diverting while roads are closed. Light rail services will not run between Circular Quay and Town Hall during the Dawn Service. Visit transportnsw.info for details.

properties.otherAdvice:
Major city roads are now closed for the Anzac Day Dawn Service in Martin Place and March down Elizabeth St in the Sydney CBD. Roads will reopen by 4pm.

The Dawn Service at the Martin Place Cenotaph is invite-only with limited general public seating for registered ticket holders only. The March on Elizabeth St will be open to spectators. March participants and spectators will be required to check in via QR code on arrival. Visit RSL NSW for details.

KEY ROAD CLOSURES

  • *CLOSED* From 2am to 4pm: roads around Martin Place including George and Pitt streets between Hunter and King streets.
  • *CLOSED* From 6am to 4pm: key roads along and surrounding the march route between Bridge St and Goulburn St including sections of Castlereagh, Elizabeth, King, Market, Hunter, Bent, Park, Bathurst, Phillip and Liverpool Streets.

Pedestrian crossing of the March route will be maintained on Hunter St at Elizabeth St and along the march route on Elizabeth St at Park St, Bathurst St and Liverpool St. 

The pop up cycleway on Pitt St is closed from 6am to 4pm between Bridge and King St.

Special event clearway parking restrictions are now in effect on various roads in the Sydney CBD from 1am to 4pm on sections of Clarence St and Pitt St and from 5:30am to 4pm on major roads between Bridge St and Goulburn St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones and apply even to local residents, businesses or RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies so check signs carefully on the day and the night before as clearways come into effect in the early morning.

Special event clearways will be in effect from 1pm to 7pm on sections of Moore Park Rd, Albion St, Lang Rd, Chalmers St, Fitzroy St, Flinders St and Foveaux St.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

properties.headline: Greek Easter Services - Sunday 25 April to Saturday 1 May - BURWOOD Railway Parade and Burleigh Street
properties.otherAdvice:

Sunday 25 April

  • Burleigh St will be closed from Railway Pde to the driveway of 24 Railway Pde from 9.30am until 11.30am. 

Friday 30 April 

  • Railway Pde from Burwood Rd to Shaftesbury Rd, and Burleigh St from Railway Pde to Elizabeth St will be closed from 8pm to 9pm. 
  • Rolling road closures will be in place on sections of Railway Pde, Burwood Rd, Belmore St and Shaftesbury Rd between 9pm and 10pm.
  • Railway Pde will close again at the conclusion of the procession between Burwood Rd and Shaftesbury Rd from 10pm to 11pm. 

Saturday 1 May

  • Railway Pde from Burwood Rd to Shaftesbury Rd, and Burleigh St from Elizabeth St to Railway Pde will be closed from 11pm until 12:30am Sunday 2 May. 

Motorists are advised to allow extra travel time and follow the directions of traffic control on site.
